issue.title: Use table mappings for FromSql

repository.name: efcore
repository.description: EF Core is a modern object-database mapper for .NET. It supports LINQ queries, change tracking, updates, and schema migrations.

issue.body:
The difference between the DbSet queries (work) and the FromSql queries (don't work) is that the DbSet queries use the table mappings, while the FromSql queries use the default mappings. The default mappings don't contain complex types. This may be an issue in of itself.

Fixes #32699

issue.body:
Replaces #32816
Fixes #32699

As discussed, leaving FromSql to use the default mappings, but add complex types to the default mappings.

issue.title: [release/8.0] Add complex type mappings to the default relational mappings

repository.name: efcore
repository.description: EF Core is a modern object-database mapper for .NET. It supports LINQ queries, change tracking, updates, and schema migrations.

issue.body:
Port of #32867
Fixes #32699

### Description

Raw SQL queries with `FromSql` use different default type mappings than other queries. These mappings were not correctly updated for complex types, a new feature in 8.0.

### Customer impact

`FromSql` queries for entity types that contain complex types will throw.

### How found

Customer reported on 8.

### Regression

No, complex types is a new feature in 8.

### Testing

Tests added.

### Risk

Low. Quirked.

body:
I am facing the same issue. As soon as I remove my complex type property from my entity, `FromSql` works as expected.
We are using EF Core 8.0.1 

But I could see that in 8.0.8 this issue does not occur anymore.
